author: Alicia Fabbre
title: Plainfield woman stabbed to death, suspect walks onto I-55 and is killed, cops say - Chicago
text:
A 47-year-old Plainfield woman was stabbed to death in a domestic-related incident and the person suspected of killing her later died after he walked out into traffic on Interstate 55, just north of Route 126, police said.
Plainfield police discovered the woman's body when responding to a welfare check in the 25000 block of Prairie Grove Court about 8 p.m. Tuesday, according to a news release. The woman was pronounced dead at Rush Copley Hospital in Aurora.
A short time later, the suspect was killed after he walked out into the northbound lanes of traffic on Interstate 55, just north of Route 126, according to authorities. The accident is being investigated by the Illinois State Police.
Police said there do not appear to be any other suspects in the homicide and they have not had any prior contact with the two people.
Authorities were not releasing the identities of the two people until relatives could be notified. Additional information is expected later today.
Alicia Fabbre is a freelance reporter.
